http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/kozhikode/KSEB-to-open-training-centre/article13980113.ece

: The Kerala State Electricity Board (KSEB) will open an exclusive training centre for its staff at Thalakkulathur. According to officials, the training centre will come up close to the proposed solar power plant project in the area. A.K. Saseendran, MLA, said the proposal submitted by the KSEB had already got the nod of the government and works would begin shortly. Mr. Saseendran, who first approached the government with the proposal, also shared that the solar power plant and training centre would be an asset for the KSEB to boost its activities in the Malabar region.